description:
secretx-systemd/src/lib.rs has the literal "systemd" duplicated in five locations:

  - line 73: `if parsed.backend() != "systemd"`
  - line 75: format string `\`systemd\`` (in error message)
  - line 97: `SecretError::Unavailable { backend: "systemd", ... }`
  - line 114: `SecretError::Backend { backend: "systemd", ... }`
  - line 126: `BackendRegistration { name: "systemd", ... }`

Engineering basis (not pure stylistic): a typo in any one occurrence (e.g. "systemd " with trailing space) would silently break dispatch. The inventory registration uses one literal, the from_uri check uses another, the error variants use a third. A divergence between line 73 and line 126 means: the URI is dispatched here but rejected by from_uri. A divergence between line 73 and line 114 means: get() reports Backend errors with a name that is not the registered name, and tooling that filters by backend would miss them. A const collapses all five into one source of truth that the compiler verifies.

Suggested fix:

  const BACKEND: &str = "systemd";

  // line 73
  if parsed.backend() != BACKEND { ... }
  // line 75 — using named-formatter args
  format!("expected backend \`{BACKEND}\`, got \`{}\`", parsed.backend())
  // lines 97, 114, 126
  backend: BACKEND, // / name: BACKEND,

Workspace-wide pattern; sibling crates have the same duplication. Worth fixing per crate as it gets reviewed.
